               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-240-person2275">
                  JOHN 
                  NAPIER
               <interp inst="t18200918-240-person2275" type="surname" value="NAPIER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-240-person2275" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-240-person2275" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Grand Junction-street, Whitefriars. On the 22d of August, at half-past four o'clock, I was in <placeName id="t18200918-240-crimeloc1385">St. James's-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-240-crimeloc1385" type="placeName" value="St. James's-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-240-crimeloc1385" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-240-off1383 t18200918-240-crimeloc1385"></join>, and felt my watch going from my pocket, a great many people were about. I looked down and saw the prisoner pulling it from my pocket, and saw it in his hand. I seized his hand with it, he stooped down and dropped it. Butcher picked it up. I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-240-person2276">
                  JOHN 
                  BUTCHER
               <interp inst="t18200918-240-person2276" type="surname" value="BUTCHER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-240-person2276" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-240-person2276" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a carpenter. I was in the square facing Mr. Napier, and saw him seize the prisoner round the waist. I saw the watch at his heels. I forced myself down and got it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-240-person2277">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HURST
               <interp inst="t18200918-240-person2277" type="surname" value="HURST"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-240-person2277" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-240-person2277" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Richards's-buildings, Shirelane. I was with Mr. Napier, he missed his watch, we both seized the prisoner. I saw him drop it.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in the square, a parcel of people shoved me into the prosecutor's hands, and said I had robbed him.</p>
               <p>
